{"word":"κοιλία","slug":"κοιλία","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κοιλία</b></el> <el>(κοιλία, ἡ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κοῖλος'><el>κοῖλος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>the large cavity of the body, the belly</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>venter</el>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>the intestines, bowels</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; <el>κ. ὑεία</el> pig's <i>tripe</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <i>tripe and puddings</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}